Abstract: In this paper we examine a representative agent forecasting prices 
 in a first-order self-referential overlapping generations model. We first consider
 intermediate stage learning, where agents update the forecasting rule every
 periods. We show that, in theory and simulations, the learning rule does not 
 converge to the rational expectations equilibrium (REE). We next consider two 
 stage learning, where agents learn the functional mapping between the current 
 forecast function and the previous forecast function. We show that in theory and 
 simulations the two stage learning rule converges to the REE.
Classification-JEL: D83, D84, E31
