Abstract: The paper commences by a discussion of the philosophical foundation of the
 concept of time. Since the concept of equilibrium is inextricably connected with that of
 time, it is argued that economists should be (more) careful when applying the equilibrium
 method; it is not legitimate to apply the concept of equilibrium without an explicit
